item.title: GBNN
item.description: Paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/1909.12098 GitHub Repository link: https://github.com/GAA-UAM/GBNN GBNN is a python library for dealing with classification (Binary and multi-class) and regression problems.

item.title: GBNN-MO
item.description: GitHub Repository link: https://github.com/GAA-UAM/GBNN-MO Gradient Boosted Neural Network-Multi-Output or GBNN-MO model is a novel training procedure for shallow and deep neural networks. The GBNN-MO is specifically developed for single and multi-output regression problems. The GBNN-MO is developed over the GBNN. model.

item.title: TFBT.BoostedTree
item.description: GitHub Repository link: https://github.com/samanemami/TFBoostedTree A gradient boosting classifier based on the tensorflow. A wrapper of the tf.BoostedTree of tensorflow based on the Sklearn standard. This model, unlike the TF method, has fit and score methods. Therefore, one can implement gridsearchCV or pipeline as well.

item.title: Input space expansion Base line
item.description: GitHub Repository link: https://github.com/samanemami/Input_space_expansion_Base_line In this project, I implemented a baseline for the "Multi-target regression via input space expansion: treating targets as inputs" (Spyromitros-Xioufis, Eleftherios, et al.) experiments. Having a baseline for the reference experiment brings more insight into the advantages of using output as an input in the model. This _multivariate class includes three different experiments as follows; Normal regression, Predicting output via other outputs, Augmenting input with the output.

item.title: Input space expansion
item.description: GitHub Repository link: https://github.com/samanemami/Input_space_expansion The focus of this project is to reproduce the two well-known multioutput regression models. The SST and ERC are introduced by Spyromitros-Xioufis, Eleftherios, et al. The main work is presented in Java here.
